13 Section 1. Section 82-4-231, MCA, is amended to read:
14 "82-4-231. Submission of and action on reclamation plan. (1) As rapidly, completely, and
15 effectively as the most modern technology and the most advanced state of the art will allow, each operator
16 granted a permit under this part shall reclaim and revegetate the land affected by the operation, except that
17 underground tunnels, shafts, or other subsurface excavations need not be revegetated. Under the provisions of
18 this part and rules adopted by the department, an operator shall prepare and carry out a method of operation, a
19 plan of grading, backfilling, highwall reduction, subsidence stabilization, water control, and topsoiling and a
20 reclamation plan for the area of land affected by the operation. In developing a method of operation and plans
21 of grading, backfilling, highwall reduction, subsidence stabilization, water control, topsoiling, and reclamation, all
22 measures must be taken to eliminate damages to landowners and members of the public, their real and
23 personal property, public roads, streams, and all other public property from soil erosion, subsidence, landslides,
24 water pollution, and hazards dangerous to life and property.
25 (2) The reclamation plan must set forth in detail the manner in which the applicant intends to
26 comply with 82-4-232 through 82-4-234 and this section and the steps to be taken to comply with applicable air
27 and water quality laws and rules and any applicable health and safety standards.
28 (3) The application for a permit or major revision of a permit, which must contain the reclamation
