15 The hearing must be started within 30 days of the request. For purposes of a hearing, the board or its hearings
16 officer may order site inspections of the area pertinent to the application. The board shall within 20 days of the
17 hearing notify the person who requested the hearing, by certified mail, and all other persons, by regular mail, of
18 the findings and decisions. A person who presided at the informal conference may not preside at the hearing or
19 participate in the decision.
20 (10) In addition to the method of operation, grading, backfilling, highwall reduction, subsidence
21 stabilization, water control, topsoiling, and reclamation requirements of this part and rules adopted under this
22 part, the operator, consistent with the directives of subsection (1), shall:
23 (a) bury under adequate fill all toxic materials, shale, mineral, or any other material determined by
24 the department to be acid-producing, toxic, undesirable, or creating a hazard;
25 (b) as directed by rules, seal off tunnels, shafts, or other openings or any breakthrough of water
26 creating a hazard;
27 (c) impound, drain, or treat all runoff or underground mine waters so as to reduce soil erosion,
28 damage to grazing and agricultural lands, and pollution of surface and subsurface waters;
