5 (f) adopt measures to prevent land subsidence unless the department approves a plan for
6 inducing subsidence into an abandoned operation in a predictable and controlled manner, with measures for
7 grading, topsoiling, and revegetating the subsided land surface. In order for a controlled subsidence plan to be
8 approved, the applicant is required to show that subsidence will not cause a direct or indirect hazard to any
9 public or private buildings, roads, facilities, or use areas, constitute a hazard to human life or health or to
10 domestic livestock or a viable agricultural operation, or violate any other restrictions the department may
11 consider necessary.
12 (g) stockpile and protect from erosion all mining and processing wastes until these wastes can be
13 disposed of according to the provisions of this part;
14 (h) deposit as much stockpiled waste material as possible back into the mine voids upon
15 abandonment in a manner that will prevent or minimize land subsidence. The remaining waste material must be
16 disposed of as provided by this part and the rules of the department.
17 (i) seal all portals, entryways, drifts, shafts, or other openings between the surface and
18 underground mine workings when no longer needed;
19 (j) to the extent possible using the best technology currently available, minimize disturbances and
20 adverse impacts of the operation on fish, wildlife, and related environmental values and achieve enhancement
21 of those resources when practicable;
22 (k) minimize the disturbances to the prevailing hydrologic balance at the mine site and in adjacent
23 areas and to the quality and quantity of water in surface water and ground water systems both during and after
24 strip- or underground-coal-mining operations and during reclamation by:
25 (i) avoiding acid or other toxic mine drainage by measures including but not limited to:
26 (A) preventing or removing water from contact with toxic-producing deposits;
27 (B) treating drainage to reduce toxic content that adversely affects downstream water upon being
28 released to watercourses;
